  <priority-name nil="true"></priority-name>
  <original-body>I have found regression in current 2.3 edge.

After this commit http://github.com/rails/rails/commit/7259baab4722d2343cbd0d81cb2aacc95d0c9461 in development environment query_cache will be always false.

It's because Dispatcher#reload_application is reset all subclasses on request.

ActiveRecord::Base.reset_subclasses if defined?(ActiveRecord)

This of course only happens for default finds without Model.cache block, that is always defined after reset of subclasses.</original-body>
